Reasoning: The paper deals with a communication network with fading channels and proposes buffer-aided relaying schemes with adaptive link selection for fixed and mixed rate transmission. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers delay constraints and develops protocols to achieve a predefined average delay, which is relevant to the systems and control community (cs.SY). The proposed schemes involve transmission and selection of nodes based on signal-to-noise ratios (SNRs), which is a key aspect of communication systems (cs.COMM). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential for multiplexing gain loss in half-duplex relaying compared to full-duplex relaying, which is relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM).
